From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] drivers/ps4: fix bpcie-icc ioread/iowrite pointer types

`bpcie_init_usb()` declares `u32 addr;` then passes `addr` to
`ioread32()`/`iowrite32()`, which expect `void __iomem *`. On strict
type-checking compilers (modern GCC/Clang) this fails with
"-Wint-conversion" turned into an error. The variable should always
have been a memory pointer.

This bug exists in both whitehax0r's 5.4 squash and crashniels' 6.15
trees and has bitten the project at every modern build. We carry the
fix as a small dedicated patch here rather than the previous workaround
of an in-place sed in build.sh.

---
diff --git a/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c b/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
--- a/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
+++ b/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
@@ -283,7 +283,7 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(bpcie_icc_cmd);

 static void bpcie_init_usb(struct bpcie_dev *sc, int usb_no) {
 	u32 value_to_write;
-	u32 addr;
+	void __iomem *addr;
 	u32 offset;

 	offset = usb_no ? 0x68 : 0x64;
